items.name: Shrek
items.description:
After 160 models, 249 followers, 29K downloads, thanks to the 9 supporters who made it possible.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Exclusive models are also available on my Patreon.

Shrek is a 2001 American computer-animated fantasy comedy film loosely based on the 1990 children's picture book of the same name by William Steig.

Prompt : Shrek, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Shrek:0.8>

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration not activated.

Use Shrek as trigger.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Shrek:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Shrek:0.8>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!

items.name: Rise of the White Flower
items.description:
DISCLAIMER: I am NOT affiliated with Necro Bunny Studios in any way. I just liked the game, scraped a bunch of images from the internet and created this model.

This is an art style from the game Rise of the White Flower by Necro Bunny Studios

Trained almost exclusively on NSFW scenes from the game, but it's perfectly capable of generating SFW images in the similar art style as well.

Most main characters are present in the training data, but since most scenes are with Catherine (tagged "cath"), she's represented the best. It's definitely possible to make the model that supports all of the characters in different circumstances, but that takes a lot of work. I might do that in the future if I find the time and motivation, but don't hold your breath for it :)

For now, just enjoy the overall art style. See the model metadata for various tags that were used during training, but again, most of the dataset is sex scenes.

Trained on AnyLora, but results are very similar on most anime-like checkpoints I've tried. Semi-realistic checkpoints like Perfect World work great too, but realistic checkpoints don't mix that well.

You should use Clip Skip 2, as is the standard for most anime-like checkpoints.

items.name: Belly Button Remover
items.description:
This model removes belly buttons. No keyword required.

How it was trained:

  • Lora overtrained on an image

  • Second lora overtrained on an edit of that image (in this case the belly button was inpainted out)

  • Repeated the above a few times

  • Merged all the loras trained on edited images into checkpoint_a

  • Merged all the loras trained on unedited images into checkpoint_b

  • Extracted lora from checkpoint_a - checkpoint_b

  • Zeroed out non-required blocks in the lora using trial and error to reduce lora side effects on generated image

Used the following guide:

https://civitai.com/models/98334/difflorafaceshadowtweaker

https://1lemon1lemon.netlify.app/2023-06-27_difflora/

Used this for training:

https://github.com/bmaltais/kohya_ss

Used the following command for overtraining loras (paths replaced with ...):

accelerate launch --num_cpu_threads_per_process=2 "train_network.py" --enable_bucket --pretrained_model_name_or_path="..." --train_data_dir="..." --resolution="768,768" --output_dir="..." --logging_dir="..." --network_alpha="16" --save_model_as=safetensors --network_module=networks.lora --unet_lr=0.001 --network_train_unet_only --network_dim=32 --output_name="01a" --lr_scheduler_num_cycles="1" --learning_rate="0.001" --lr_scheduler="constant" --train_batch_size="1" --max_train_steps="400" --save_every_n_epochs="1" --mixed_precision="fp16" --save_precision="fp16" --cache_latents --optimizer_type="AdamW8bit" --max_data_loader_n_workers="0" --bucket_reso_steps=64 --xformers --bucket_no_upscale

items.name: Digital camera models wildcard
items.description:
A wildcard model of the following digital camera manufacturers:

  • Hasselblad, Canon, and Fujifilm (1.0)

  • Olympus, Sanyo, and Sony (appended with 1.0 to form 2.0)

  • Apple, Samsung, Sony Ericsson and ZTE (3.0)

It includes camera models from the 2000's to 2023. This is the first release in a series of camera models and will appended in later versions. The list was compiled with data from ExifTool and each manufacturer has their own wildcard.

To simulate the quality of low fidelity images with earlier or lower end models, it's best to use a Lora that specializes itself in that category such as : Low quality (hof)

Or use a negative embedding in the positive prompt with a very low weight. Its effect may or may not work properly depending on the base model or the embedding itself.

items.name: Belko Style
items.description:
A versatile anime style with bright colors. Works great as a general style LoRA when you're not after specific features.

How to use
Just prompt your cute anime girls as normal. The dataset is fairly mixed so most themes and tags should work fine though the LoRA has a tendency to put big breasts on everyone unless prompted otherwise.

MISC
Trained on AOM2 at 512px with 234 images.
All images are raw txt2img upscaled without inpainting or any helper embeddings.
Note that the LoRA was trained on a small subset of female character images and isn't an accurate representation of the artist's style. If you want the high quality latest and greatest stuff you can go support the artist here.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

items.name: Gene Hackman Lora
items.description:
Be nice, have fun!

Eugene Allen Hackman[1][2][3] (born January 30, 1930) is an American retired actor and novelist. In a career that spanned more than six decades, Hackman has received two Academy Awards, two BAFTA Awards, four Golden Globes, a Screen Actors Guild Award, and the Silver Bear. Hackman's two Academy Awards wins include one for Best Actor for his role as Jimmy "Popeye" Doyle in William Friedkin's acclaimed thriller The French Connection (1971), and the other for Best Supporting Actor playing "Little" Bill Daggett in Clint Eastwood's Western film Unforgiven (1992). His other Oscar-nominated roles were in Bonnie and Clyde (1967), I Never Sang for My Father (1970), and Mississippi Burning (1988).

Hackman gained notoriety for his portrayal as Lex Luthor in Superman (1978) and its sequels Superman II (1980) and Superman IV: The Quest for Peace (1987). His also acted in The Poseidon Adventure (1972), The Conversation (1974), Reds (1981), Hoosiers (1986), No Way Out (1987), Get Shorty (1995), Crimson Tide (1995), The Birdcage (1996), Absolute Power (1997), and The Royal Tenenbaums (2001).

items.name: Nythia Menon (gorgeous indian actress and singer)
items.description:
By request of a civitai's user, this LyCORIS has been trained after carefully selecting 81 images. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them.

Nithya Menon (born 8 April 1988) is an Indian actress and singer who has acted in more than 50 feature films in various languages. She appeared first on-screen as a child, when she was ten, in the French-Indian English film, Hanuman (1998), playing the younger sister to Tabu's character. She started her acting career at the age of 17 by appearing in a supporting role in the Kannada film 7 O' Clock, which was released in 2006. She has played leading roles in Malayalam in Aakasha Gopuram (2008), in Telugu in Ala Modalaindi (2011), in Tamil with Nootrenbadhu (2011), and in Hindi in Mission Mangal (2019).

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) that would be highly appreciated! Please press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

From my experience it runs best with ICBINP - "I Can't Believe It's Not Photography", Edge Of Realism, pirsusEpicRealism, epicDiffusion, RealisticVision, CyberRealistic, Deliberate checkpoints, among others, although I think it will be just fine in other SD 1.5 models as well.

CFG scale should be between 4-7.

LyCORIS weights should be between 1-1.4

items.name: Cindy Crawford (JG)
items.description:
Cindy Crawford is an American supermodel and actress.

150-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (ccr4wf0rd:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: WaterMorph
items.description:
This piece of Lora took quite some time. Starting with simple shapes, generating other training images, etc.

In the end this model morphs your images to water. At low values it is more like a style. Different things might require different value to give the desired effect.

There is still a lot to improve, however, I'm happy to share this v1.0 with you.

Many thanks to rfktr for a lot of helpful input. :)

Reducing the weight and adding "water" to the prompt improves the results on characters.

If you like what I'm creating feel free to buy me a coffee.

I'd like to see your creations, too. Leave a review of your colorful images.
